{"title_page": "Kris Holden-Ried", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name = Kris Holden-Ried\n| image = Kristen Holden-Ried at Fan Expo 1.jpg\n| caption = Holden-Ried at the August 2011 [[Fan Expo Canada|Fan Expo]]\n| birth_name = Kristen Holden-Ried\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1973|8|1|mf=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Pickering, Ontario]], Canada\n| occupation = Actor\n| years_active = 1995\u2013present\n| children = 1\n}}\n\n'''Kris Holden-Ried''' (born August 1, 1973) is a Canadian actor.\n\n==Early life and pentathlon==\nHolden-Ried was born in [[Pickering, Ontario]].{{citation needed|date=November 2015}} He studied at [[Montreal]]'s [[Concordia University]] School of Business.<ref name=post>{{cite web|title=The man behind Captain Canuck\u2019s mask|url=http://postcity.com/Eat-Shop-Do/Do/August-2013/The-man-behind-Captain-Canucks-mask/|website=postcity.com|accessdate=19 March 2017|language=en}}</ref> He was a champion competitor in [[equestrianism|riding]] and [[fencing]],<ref name=globe>{{cite web|title=Sporty wagon suits athletic actor and his family|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/globe-drive/culture/commuting/sporty-wagon-suits-athletic-actor-and-his-family/article4258743/|website=The Globe and Mail|accessdate=19 March 2017|language=en-ca}}</ref> and is a former member of the Canadian National Pentathlon Team<ref name=post /> and has a [[silver medal]] from both the Pan American and Pan Pacific Pentathlon Championships.<ref name=globe />\n\n==Career==\nAt his first audition, he landed the leading role in 12th century drama, ''[[Young Ivanhoe]]''.<ref name=post /> In 2007, he portrayed [[William Compton (The Tudors)|William Compton]] in the first seven episodes of the [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]] series ''[[The Tudors]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=INTERVIEW: Lost Girl & Underworlds Kris Holden-Ried|url=http://www.gamesradar.com/interview-lost-girl-underworldkris-holden-ried/|website=gamesradar|accessdate=19 March 2017|language=en}}</ref> In 2010, he began appearing in the television series ''[[Lost Girl (TV series)|Lost Girl]]'' as Dyson.<ref name=lost>{{cite web|title=Kris Holden-Ried Talks LOST GIRL and UNDERWORLD: AWAKENING|url=http://collider.com/kris-holden-ried-lost-girl-underworld-4-interview/|website=Collider|accessdate=19 March 2017|date=13 January 2012}}</ref> He played Quint Lane, the 'super lycan', in the film ''[[Underworld: Awakening]]'' (2012).<ref name=lost />  In 2013, he voiced [[Captain Canuck]] in the animated web series of the same name.<ref name=post /> Holden-Ried provided the voice for the character Crawford Starrick, the main antagonist; on the hit video game ''[[Assassin's Creed: Syndicate]]''.\n\n==Personal life==\nHolden-Ried has one child, a son.<ref name=globe />\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n|1995||Young Invanhoe||Ivanhoe||TV Movie\n|-\n|1996||[[Rowing Through]]||Kurt Cruise||Film\n|-\n|1997||[[Habitat]]||Daryl||Film\n|-\n|1997||When Innocence Is Lost||Kevin||TV Movie\n|-\n|1997||''[[Night of the Demons 3]]''||Vince||Film\n|-\n|1997||[[Riverdale_(1997_TV_series)|Riverdale]]||Shawn Ritchie||Unknown\n|-\n|1998||[[Going to Kansas City]]||Charlie Bruckner||Film\n|-\n|1998||The Defenders: Taking the First||McCann||TV Movie\n|-\n|1999||Forget Me Never||Unknown||TV Movie\n|-\n|1999||[[Twice in a Lifetime (TV series)|Twice in a Lifetime]]||Young Ken Stryker||Episode: \u201cO\u2019er the Ramparts We Watched\u201d\n|-\n|2000||[[The Crossing (2000 film)|The Crossing]]||Capt. Heineman||TV Movie\n|-\n|2000||[[Gossip_(2000_American_film)|Gossip]]||Bruce||Film\n|-\n|2000||Hendrix||Noel Redding||TV Movie\n|-\n|2000||Girls Who Say Yes||Matt||Short\n|-\n|2000||[[The Secret Adventures of Jules Verne]]||George Custer||Episode: \u201cThe Rocket\u2019s Red Glare\u201d\n|-\n|2001||Chasing Cain||Troy||TV Movie\n|-\n|2001||[[Paradise Falls]]||Simon||Recurring (Season 1)\n|-\n|2001-2004||[[Degrassi: The Next Generation]]||Tucker Cameron||Recurring (Sea