 Girl & Underworlds Kris Holden-Ried|url=http://www.gamesradar.com/interview-lost-girl-underworldkris-holden-ried/|website=gamesradar|accessdate=19 March 2017|language=en}}</ref> In 2010, he began appearing in the television series ''[[Lost Girl (TV series)|Lost Girl]]'' as Dyson.<ref name=lost>{{cite web|title=Kris Holden-Ried Talks LOST GIRL and UNDERWORLD: AWAKENING|url=http://collider.com/kris-holden-ried-lost-girl-underworld-4-interview/|website=Collider|accessdate=19 March 2017|date=13 January 2012}}</ref> He played Quint Lane, the 'super lycan', in the film ''[[Underworld: Awakening]]'' (2012).<ref name=lost />  In 2013, he voiced [[Captain Canuck]] in the animated web series of the same name.<ref name=post /> Holden-Ried provided the voice for the character Crawford Starrick, the main antagonist; on the hit video game ''[[Assassin's Creed: Syndicate]]''.\n\n==Personal life==\nHolden-Ried has one child, a son.<ref name=globe />\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n|1995||Young Invanhoe||Ivanhoe||TV Movie\n|-\n|1996||[[Rowing Through]]||Kurt Cruise||Film\n|-\n|1997||[[Habitat]]||Daryl||Film\n|-\n|1997||When Innocence Is Lost||Kevin||TV Movie\n|-\n|1997||''[[Night of the Demons 3]]''||Vince||Film\n|-\n|1997||[[Riverdale_(1997_TV_series)|Riverdale]]||Shawn Ritchie||Unknown\n|-\n|1998||[[Going to Kansas City]]||Charlie Bruckner||Film\n|-\n|1998||The Defenders: Taking the First||McCann||TV Movie\n|-\n|1999||Forget Me Never||Unknown||TV Movie\n|-\n|1999||[[Twice in a Lifetime (TV series)|Twice in a Lifetime]]||Young Ken Stryker||Episode: \u201cO\u2019er the Ramparts We Watched\u201d\n|-\n|2000||The Crossing||Capt. Heineman||TV Movie\n|-\n|2000||[[Gossip_(2000_American_film)|Gossip]]||Bruce||Film\n|-\n|2000||Hendrix||Noel Redding||TV Movie\n|-\n|2000||Girls Who Say Yes||Matt||Short\n|-\n|2000||[[The Secret Adventures of Jules Verne]]||George Custer||Episode: \u201cThe Rocket\u2019s Red Glare\u201d\n|-\n|2001||Chasing