lio Crisosto]]\n|1971\u20131977\n|11\n|27\n|{{#expr:11/27 round 2}}\n|- align=center\n|rowspan=4|19.\n|align=left|[[Atilio Cremaschi]]\n|1945\u20131954\n|10\n|31\n|{{#expr:10/31 round 2}}\n|- align=center\n|align=left|[[Ren\u00e9 Mel\u00e9ndez]]\n|1950\u20131960\n|10\n|39\n|{{#expr:10/39 round 2}}\n|- align=center\n|align=left|[[Reinaldo Navia]]\n|1999\u20132007\n|10\n|40\n|{{#expr:10/40 round 2}}\n|- align=center\n|align=left|[[Jaime Ram\u00edrez]]\n|1954\u20131966\n|10\n|46\n|{{#expr:10/46 round 2}}\n|- align=center\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n{{Col-begin}}\n{{Col-break}}\n[[File:Alexis_Sanchez_-_Spain_vs._Chile,_10th_September_2013_(cropped).jpg|180px|thumb|center|Alexis S\u00e1nchez is the top scorer in the history of Chile with 43 goals, and the most capped player with 132 caps.]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Competitive record==\n{{Main|Chile national football team head to head}}\n\n===FIFA World Cup===\n{{Main|Chile at the FIFA World Cup}}\n\n{{Color box|gold|border=darkgray}} '''Champions'''&nbsp;&nbsp;{{Color box|silver|border=darkgray}} '''Runners-up'''&nbsp;&nbsp;{{Color box|#cc9966|border=darkgray}} Third Place&nbsp;&nbsp;{{Color box|LemonChiffon|border=darkgray}} Fourth Place&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!colspan=9|[[FIFA World Cup]] record\n!width=1% rowspan=26|\n!colspan=6|[[FIFA World Cup qualification]] record\n|-\n!Year\n!Round\n!Position\n!{{Tooltip|Pld|Games played}}\n!{{Tooltip|W|Won}}\n!{{Tooltip|D|Drawn}}*\n!{{Tooltip|L|Lost}}\n!{{Tooltip|GF|Goals for}}\n!{{Tooltip|GA|Goals against}}\n!{{Tooltip|Pld|Games played}}\n!{{Tooltip|W|Won}}\n!{{Tooltip|D|Drawn}}\n!{{Tooltip|L|Lost}}\n!{{Tooltip|GF|Goals for}}\n!{{Tooltip|GA|Goals against}}\n|-\n| {{flagicon|Uruguay}} [[1930 FIFA World Cup|1930]]\n| Group stage\n| 5th\n| 3\n| 2\n| 0\n| 1\n| 5\n| 3\n| colspan=6|''Qualified as invitees''\n|-\n| {{flagicon|Italy|1861}} [[1934 FIFA World Cup|1934]]\n| colspan=8 rowspan=2|''Withdrew''\n| colspan=6 rowspan=2|''Withdrew''\n|-\n| {{flagicon