eter)|Dean Jones]]\n| Head coach \n|-\n|-\n| {{flagicon|PAK}} [[Wasim Akram]]\n| Bowling Mentor & President<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://pakistansuperleaguepsl.com/psl-4-wasim-akram-joins-karachi-kings-as-president/|title=PSL 4: Wasim Akram Joins Karachi Kings as President|date=2018-11-14|work=Live Cricket Streaming Online|access-date=2018-11-14|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|PAK}} [[Faisal Iqbal]]\n| Batting coach\n|-\n|{{flagicon|AUS}} [[Johan Botha (cricketer)|Johan Botha]]\n|Assistant Coach\n|-\n|{{flagicon|PAK}} Faisal Mirza\n|Media manager<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.baaghitv.com/faisal-mirza-takes-over-as-new-media-manager-of-karachi-kings/|title=Faisal Mirza takes over as new Media Manager of Karachi Kings|author=Mehreen Saqib|work=baaghi Tv|date=29 January 2020|accessdate=16 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|PAK}} Ibrahim Qureshi\n| Fitness trainer\n|-\n|}\n\n==Captains==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:mediumblue; color:red\" | No.\n! style=\"background:mediumblue; color:red;\"| Nat.\n! style=\"background:mediumblue; color:red\" | Player\n! style=\"background:mediumblue; color:red\" | From\n! style=\"background:mediumblue; color:red\" | To\n! style=\"background:mediumblue; color:red\" | {{Tooltip|Mat|No. of Matches as Captain}}\n! style=\"background:mediumblue; color:red\" | {{Tooltip|Won|Won}}\n! style=\"background:mediumblue; color:red\" | {{Tooltip|Lost|Lost}}\n! style=\"background:mediumblue; color:red\" | {{Tooltip|Tie&W|Tied}}\n! style=\"background:mediumblue; color:red\" | {{Tooltip|Tie&L|Tied}}\n! style=\"background:mediumblue; color:red\" | {{Tooltip|NR|No Result}}\n! style=\"background:mediumblue; color:red\" | {{Tooltip|%|Win Percentage}}\n|-\n| 1\n| {{flagicon|PAK}}\n| [[Shoaib Malik]]\n| 2016\n| 2016\n| 8\n| 2\n| 6\n| 0\n| 0\n| 0\n| 25.00\n|-\n| 2\n| {{flagicon|ENG}}\n| [[Ravi Bopara]]\n| 2016\n| 2016\n| 1\n| 0\n| 1\n| 0\n| 0\n| 0\n| 0.00\n|-\n| 3\n|{{flagicon|SRI}}\n| [[Kumar Sangakkara]]\n| 2017\n| 2017\n| 10\n| 5\n| 5\n| 0\n| 0\n| 0\n| 50.00\n|-\n| 4\n|{{flagicon|PAK}}\n| [[Imad Wasim]]\n| 2018\n| present\n| 28\n| 14\n| 11\n| 0\n| 1\n| 2\n| 55.76\n|-\n| 5\n|{{flagicon|ENG}}\n| [[Eoin Morgan]]\n| 2018\n| 2018\n| 3\n| 1\n| 2\n| 0\n| 0\n| 0\n| 33.33\n|-\n| 6\n|{{flagicon|PAK}}\n| [[Mohammad Amir]]\n| 2018\n| 2018\n| 1\n| 0\n| 1\n| 0\n| 0\n| 0\n| 0.00\n|-\n| 7\n|{{flagicon|PAK}}\n| [[Babar Azam]]\n| 2020\n| 2020\n| 1\n| 0\n| 1\n| 0\n| 0\n| 0\n| 0.00\n|}\n\n<small>Source: [http://stats.espncricinfo.com/pakistan-super-league-2016-17/engine/records/individual/most_matches_as_captain.html?id=205;team=5793;type=trophy ESPNcricinfo], Last updated: 15 March 2020</small>\n\n==Result summary==\n===Overall result in PSL===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Pld !! Won !! {{Tooltip | Loss | Matches Loss }} !! Tie&W !!Tie&L !! {{Tooltip | NR | No Result}} !! {{Tooltip | SR(%) | Success Rate}} !! Position !! Summary\n|-\n! [[2016 Pakistan Super League|2016]]\n| 9|| 2|| 7|| 0||0 ||0|| 22.22 || 4/5 || Play-offs \n|-\n! [[2017 Pakistan Super League|2017]]\n| 10 ||5|| 5|| 0|| 0|| 0 || 50.00 || 3/5 || Play-offs \n|-\n! [[2018 Pakistan Super League|2018]]\n|12||5||5|| 0 ||1 || 1 ||50.50|| 3/6 || Play-offs \n|-\n! [[2019 Pakistan Super League|2019]]\n|11||5||6||0||0||0||45.45|| 4/6 || Play-offs\n|-\n! [[2020 Pakistan Super League|2020]]\n|10||5||4||0||0||1||50.00|| \u2013 || \u2013\n|-\n!  Total\n|'''52'''||'''22'''||'''27'''||'''0''' || '''1''' || '''2''' ||'''45.00'''||  || '''0 titles''' \n|}\n<small>Source: [http://stats.espncricinfo.com/pakistan-super-league-2016-17/engine/records/team/results_summary.html?id=205;type=trophy ESPNcricinfo], Last updated: 15 March 2020</small>\n\n===Head-to-head record===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Opposition!! Span !! Mat !! Won !! Lost !! Tie&W !! Tie&L !! NR !! SR%\n|-\n| [[Islamabad United]]|| 2016\u2013present ||13||5||7|| 0 || 0 || 0 ||38.46\n|-\n| [[Lahore Qalandars]]||2016\u2013present  || 9 || 5 