 form the core of the team. Players can now gain contracts for Test and limited-overs (white-ball) cricket and in some cases both.<ref name=\"Central Contracts\">{{cite web |url=https://www.ecb.co.uk/news/111456 |title=Test and White Ball central contracts offered by England |publisher=ECB |accessdate=29 September 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161005192451/https://www.ecb.co.uk/news/111456 |archive-date=5 October 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> Other players who play enough games during the year can also gain Incremental contracts.\n\n'''Key'''\n*S/N = Shirt number\n*C/T = Contract type (Test / White-ball / Incremental)\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|-\n!style=\"text-align:center;background:skyblue;color:#15295E\"| Name\n!style=\"text-align:center;background:skyblue;color:#15295E\"| Age\n!style=\"text-align:center;background:skyblue;color:#15295E\"| Batting style\n!style=\"text-align:center;background:skyblue;color:#15295E\"| Bowling style\n!style=\"text-align:center;background:skyblue;color:#15295E\"| Domestic team\n!style=\"text-align:center;background:skyblue;color:#15295E\"| C/T<ref>{{Cite web |title=ECB announces Men's Central Contracts for the 2019/20 season |url=https://www.ecb.co.uk/england/men/news/1349647/-ecb-announces-men-s-central-contracts-for-the-2019-20-season |website=ecb.co.uk |publisher=England & Wales Cricket Board |date=20 September 2019 |access-date=20 September 2019 }}</ref>\n!style=\"text-align:center;background:skyblue;color:#000060\"| Forms<!--NOTE: This refers to the forms they've played for England in the past year, not over their whole England career-->\n!style=\"text-align:center;background:skyblue;color:#000060\"| S/N<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/england/content/story/209588.html |title=ESPN Cricinfo \u2013 England ODI/Twenty Shirt Numbers |publisher=ESPNcricinfo |accessdate=1 August 2013 |date=18 May 2005 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130601075617/http://www.espncricinfo.com/england/content/story/209588.html |archive-date=1 June 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n!style=\"text-align:center;background:skyblue;color:#15295E\"| Captaincy\n!style=\"text-align:center;background:skyblue;color:#15295E\"| Last Test\n!style=\"text-align:center;background:skyblue;color:#15295E\"| Last ODI\n!style=\"text-align:center;background:skyblue;color:#15295E\"| Last T20I\n|-\n!colspan=\"12\"| Batsmen\n|-\n| [[Tom Banton]] || {{age|1998|11|11}} || Right-handed || \u2013 || [[Somerset County Cricket Club|Somerset ]] ||align=\"center\"| \u2013 || ODI, T20I ||align=\"center\"| 98 || || \u2013 || {{cricon|SA}} 2020 || {{cricon|NZL}} 2019\n|-\n| [[Rory Burns]] || {{age|1990|8|26}} || Left-handed || \u2013 || [[Surrey County Cricket Club|Surrey]] ||align=\"center\"| T || Test ||align=\"center\"| 27 || || {{cricon|SA}} 2019 || \u2013 || \u2013\n|-\n| [[Zak Crawley]] || {{age|1998|2|3}} || Right-handed || \u2013 || [[Kent County Cricket Club|Kent ]] ||align=\"center\"| \u2013 || Test ||align=\"center\"| 56 || || {{cricon|SA}} 2020 || \u2013 || \u2013\n|-\n| [[Joe Denly]] || {{age|1986|3|16}} || Right-handed || Right-arm [[leg spin]] || [[Kent County Cricket Club|Kent]] ||align=\"center\"| W || Test, ODI, T20I ||align=\"center\"| 24 || || {{cricon|SA}} 2020 || {{cricon|SA}} 2020 || {{cricon|SA}} 2020\n|-\n| [[Ben Duckett]] || {{age|1994|10|17}} || Left-handed || Right-arm [[off break]] || [[Nottinghamshire County Cricket Club|Nottinghamshire]] ||align=\"center\"| \u2013 || T20I ||align=\"center\"| 45 || || {{cricon|IND}} 2017 || {{cricon|BAN}} 2016 || {{cricon|PAK}} 2019\n|-\n| ''[[Keaton Jennings]]'' || {{age|1992|6|19}} || Left-handed || Right-arm [[Fast bowling|medium-fast]] || [[Lancashire County Cricket Club|Lancashire]] ||align=\"center\"| \u2013 || ''Test'' ||align=\"center\"| 65 || || {{cricon|WIN}} 2019 || \u2013 || \u2013\n|-\n| [[Dawid Malan]] || {{age|1987|9|3}} || Left-handed || Right-arm [[leg spin]] || [[Yorkshire County Cricket Club|Yorkshire]] ||align=\"center\"| |