ackground:LemonChiffon\"\n|{{flagicon|RSA}} [[2009 ICC Champions Trophy|2009]]||Semi-final||4/8||4||2||2||0||0||50.00\n|- style=\"background:silver\"\n|style=\"border:2px solid red\"|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[2013 ICC Champions Trophy|2013]]||Runners-up||2/8||5||3||2||0||0||60.00\n|- style=\"background:#cc9966\"\n|style=\"border:2px solid red\"|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[2017 ICC Champions Trophy|2017]]||Semi-final||3/8||4||3||1||0||0||75.00\n|-\n!Total||0 titles||8/8||24||13||11||0||0||54.17\n|}\n\n:''*The win percentage excludes no results and counts ties as half a win.''\n\n===Honours===\n*[[ICC T20 World Cup]] (1): [[2010 World Twenty20|2010]]\n*[[Cricket World Cup]] (1): [[2019 Cricket World Cup|2019]]\n\n==Records==\n{{main|England cricket team record by opponent}}\n\n===Test matches===\n{{Main|List of England Test cricket records}}\n\n====Test team records====\n*Highest team total: '''903\u20137 dec.''' v. [[Australia national cricket team|Australia]] at [[The Oval]] in 1938\n*Lowest team total: '''45''' v. Australia at [[Sydney Cricket Ground|Sydney]] in 1886/87\n*England are the only team in the history of Test cricket to have secured 100 victories by an innings\n\n====Test individual records====\n*Most matches: '''161 Tests'''&nbsp;\u2013 [[Alastair Cook]]<ref>{{citation |url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/england/engine/records/individual/most_matches_career.html?class=1;id=1;type=team |title=Most Test matches playing for England |publisher=ESPNcricinfo |access-date=3 September 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111222090717/http://stats.espncricinfo.com/england/engine/records/individual/most_matches_career.html?class=1%3Bid%3D1%3Btype%3Dteam |archive-date=22 December 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*Longest-serving captain: '''59 Tests'''&nbsp;\u2013 Alastair Cook\n\n====Test batting records====\n*Most runs: '''12,472'''&nbsp;\u2013 Alastair Cook<ref>{{citation|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/stats/index.html?class=1;team=1;template=results;type=batting|title=Most Runs for England|publisher=ESPNcricinfo|access-date=4 September 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111222090016/http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/stats/index.html?class=1%3Bteam%3D1%3Btemplate%3Dresults%3Btype%3Dbatting|archive-date=22 December 2011|url-status=live}} Retrieved on 26 January 2016.</ref>\n*Best average: '''60.73'''&nbsp;\u2013 [[Herbert Sutcliffe]]<ref>{{citation|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/batting/highest_career_batting_average.html?class=1;id=1;type=team|title=Highest Batting Averages|publisher=cricinfo.com|access-date=13 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171116193617/http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/batting/highest_career_batting_average.html?class=1;id=1;type=team|archive-date=16 November 2017|url-status=live}} Retrieved on 13 February 2019.</ref>\n*Highest individual score: '''364'''&nbsp;\u2013 [[Len Hutton]] v. Australia at [[The Oval]] in 1938\n*Record partnership: '''411'''&nbsp;\u2013 [[Colin Cowdrey]] and [[Peter May (cricketer)|Peter May]] v. [[West Indies cricket team|West Indies]] at [[Edgbaston Cricket Ground|Edgbaston]] in 1957\n*Most centuries: '''33'''&nbsp;\u2013 Alastair Cook\n*England's most prolific opening partnership was [[Jack Hobbs]] and Herbert Sutcliffe. In 38 innings, they averaged 87.81 for the first wicket, with 15 century partnerships and 10 others of 50 or more\n*Most ducks: '''35'''&nbsp;\u2013 [[Stuart Broad]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/england/engine/records/batting/most_ducks_career.html?class=1;id=1;type=team |title=Most ducks for England |publisher=ESPNcricinfo |accessdate=2 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Test bowling records====\n*Most wickets: '''584'''&nbsp;\u2013 [[James Anderson (cricketer)|James Anderson]]\n*Best average: '''10.75'''&nbsp;\u2013 [[George Lohmann]]\n*Best innings bowling: '''10/53'''&nbsp;\u2013 [[Jim Laker]] v. Australia at Old Trafford in 1956\n*Best match bowling: '''19/90'''&nbsp;\u2013 Jim Laker v. Australia at Old Trafford in 1956\n*Best [[strike rate]]: '''34.1'''&nbsp;\u2013 George Lohmann\n*Best economy rate: '''1.31'''&nbsp;\u2013 [[William Attewell]]\n*Five England bowlers have taken four wickets in an over, three of these at Headingley. They were [[Maurice Allom]] v. New Zealand at Christchurch in 1929\u201330, [[Kenneth Cranston]] v. South Africa at Headingley in 1947, [[Fred Titmus]] v. New Zealand at Headingley in 1965, [[Chris Old]] v. Pakistan at Edgbaston in 1978 and [[Andy Caddick]] v. West Indies at Headingley in 2000\n\n====Test fielding records====\n*Most catches by an outfielder: '''175'''&nbsp;\u2013 Alastair Cook\n*Most dismissals as wicketkeeper: '''269'''&nbsp;\u2013 [[Alan Knott]]\n*Most dismissals in an innings: '''7'''&nbsp;\u2013 [[Bob Taylor (cricketer)|Bob Taylor]] v. [[India national cricket team|India]] at [[Wankhede Stadium|Bombay]] in 1979/80\n*Most dismissals in a match: '''11'''&nbsp;\u2013 [[Jack Russell (cricketer and artist)|Jack Russell]] v. [[South Africa national cricket team|South Africa]] at [[Wanderers Stadium|Johannesburg]] in 1995/96\n\n====Test record versus other nations====\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;width:600px\"\n|-\n! Opponent !! M !! W !! L !! T !! D !! % Win !! First win\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| {{cr|AUS}} || 351 || 110 || 146 || 0 || 95 || 31.33 || 4 April 1877\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| {{cr|RSA}} || 153 || 64 || 34 || 0 || 55 || 41.83 || 13 March 1889\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| {{cr|WIN}} || 157 || 49 || 57 || 0 || 51 || 31.21 || 26 June 1928\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| {{cr|NZL}} || 105 || 48 || 11 || 0 || 46 || 45.71 || 13 January 1930\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| {{cr|IND}} || 122 || 47 || 26 || 0 || 49 || 38.52 || 28 June 1932\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| {{cr|PAK}} || 83 || 25 || 21|| 0 || 37 || 30.12 || 5 July 1954\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| {{cr|SRI}} || 34 || 15 || 8 || 0 || 11 || 44.11 || 21 February 1982\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| {{cr|ZIM}} || 6 || 3 || 0 || 0 || 3 || 50.00 |